FT  19 MAR 94 / Briefcase, Q&amp;A: The Queen and tax
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
I seem to recollect that when the Queen agreed voluntarily to pay capital
gains tax on her investments, the base values were to be calculated from
April 6 1993. Is this correct and, if so, why was a different date chosen
from that which applies to her subjects: viz, March 31 1982, plus
indexation.
April 6 1993 is simply the date from which the voluntary income tax and CGT
payments are to be made under the Queen's offer.
