<HEADLINE>
FT  19 MAR 94 / International Company News: French group lifts US stake
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN RIDDING
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Compagnie Generale des Eaux, the French utilities and industrial group, said
yesterday it has agreed to raise its stake in Air &amp; Water Technology of the
US from 23 per cent to 40 per cent.
As a result, it will hold 48 per cent of the voting rights of the US
company, which specialises in the treatment of water and the reduction of
air pollution, and has annual sales of about Dollars 630m.
The French group described the move as 'an important step in its strategy of
expanding in the US in areas of strong growth'. It already achieves annual
sales of about FFr5.5bn (Dollars 954m) in the US market.
Under the terms of the agreement, Generale des Eaux will exchange its
wholly-owned subsidiary, Professional Services Group, for 6.5m new Air &amp;
Water shares. The French group will also subscribe to a private placement
share issue with a priority dividend, and an issue of ordinary shares in the
US group.
