<TEXT>
Fortnum &amp; Mason food fans helped the London department store to an increase
in sales and pre-tax profits for the 28 weeks ended January 22 1994.
A better-than-expected rise in Christmas catalogue sales - the wishbook of
the famous Fortnum's hamper - helped boost operating profits by 21 per cent
