cash of Pounds 7m. This would fall after the purchase of a long leasehold
for Pounds 1.75m.
The company warned that the outlook for the second half remained uncertain.
Trading continued to be buoyant, but the vast majority of Fortnum's profits
were traditionally made in the first half.
