weak state of the real estate market and largely accounted for the rise in
losses.
Credit du Nord said that its target of breakeven for this year, with profits
in 1995 and 1996, required an increase in its capital base.
Paribas, its parent company, said it would inject FFr618m of new capital and
subscribe, at market rates, to a FFr1.5bn subordinated convertible bond
issue.
