They continued to rise throughout the day and closed at 172p with nearly 24m
traded, the heaviest turnover on the London stock market.
New issue Israel Fund, a closed end investment trust concentrating on
Israeli companies, made a successful start with a hefty turnover of 13m. The
shares that traded with a warrant attached to every five rose from 82.4 to
86 cents.
