<HEADLINE>
FT  18 MAR 94 / International Company News: Entel plans to raise Dollars
350m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID PILLING
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Entel, Chile's largest long-distance telephone operator, yesterday decided
to raise Dollars 350m through the issue of American Depository Receipts
(ADRs) in New York and shares on the Santiago exchange.
The cash is to be raised in two tranches, one this year and another in 1996,
said company spokesman Mr Marcelo Maturama. It will be used to fund the
company's expansion plans including extension of its micro-wave and
fibre-optic lines and the development of its personal telephone service.
</TEXT>
